{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6311cf64-8b3a-40e3-9610-f1d71ddc02c5","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n**1. Update package references in your `.csproj`:**\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove these -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"4.6.0\" />\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add this -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit.Runner\" Version=\"4.3.0\" /> <!-- or latest -->\n```\n\n**2. Set output type to Exe:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. Run tests with:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet run          # direct execution\ndotnet test         # still works (with --test-adapter-path auto-detected)\n```\n\n**Key notes:**\n- `NUnit.Runner` bundles the Microsoft.Testing.Platform host + NUnit adapter\n- `GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint` auto-generates `Main`; alternatively, write your own `Program.cs`\n- Keep your `NUnit` framework package as-is — your test code doesn't change\n- If you use `dotnet test`, add `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` to your project for the new protocol","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bdf509d8-1223-490c-aa03-7e17f7aa75d0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure migration. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nKey changes needed to migrate NUnit from VSTest (NUnit3TestAdapter) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. Replace `NUnit3TestAdapter` with `NUnit.Runner` (or the appropriate Microsoft.Testing.Platform-compatible adapter)\n2. Actually, for NUnit, the migration path is:\n   - Remove `NUnit3TestAdapter` \n   - Add `NUnit.Engine` and the Microsoft.Testing.Platform NUnit adapter\n   - Or use the newer approach with `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` extensions\n\nLet me think more carefully. The Microsoft.Testing.Platform is a newer test platform that replaces VSTest. For NUnit specifically, I need to remove the VSTest infrastructure packages like `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` and `NUnit3TestAdapter`, then add the NUnit team's `NUnit.Runner` package which integrates directly with Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nTo migrate, I'd remove those two packages and add `NUnit.Runner`, then change the project to an executable with `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>`. For the entry point, I can either write a `Program.cs` to set up the runner or use the MSBuild property `<GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>true</GenerateTestingPlatformEntryPoint>` to auto-generate it.","outputTokens":850,"requestId":"6807:1E8CE8:6F8BB2:76D8B2:6A044D48"},"id":"9459278b-f55b-4987-a099-d28a723b63a3","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:27.839Z","parentId":"1ad222dc-7a67-46e2-803e-8b9e7a529522"}
